1. Drool file is set of rules that are implemented in application code.
   Drool is a rule engine through which we can set rules for our application business logic
   and we can separate hardcode conditions from business logic

2. Drools is Business Rules Management System written in java.
   Business logic can be written in set of rules implementation in application code, can be managed
   without hard coding if-else conditions.

3. Rules :
         When <SomeConditon satisfied>
            <perform some action>
         Then